rlm-gh-repo-init [OWNER/REPO]

Create a private GitHub repository from the current directory and push,
provided no remote is configured yet.

The argument must be in OWNER/REPO form (e.g. ecerulm/my-project).

If no argument is provided, defaults to <github-username>/<current-dir>
(username looked up via 'gh api user') and prompts for confirmation
before continuing.

Requires: gh, git.
